{"word":"G4262 - προβατικός - probatikós - prob-at-ik-os' - Sheep","sections":[{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">προβατικός</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong><span class=\"transliteration\">probatikós</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong><span class=\"phonetic\">prob-at-ik-os'</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong><span class=\"short-definition\">Sheep</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>இலக்கண சொல்வகை / Part(s) of speech: </strong>Adjective / பெயரடை</span>"},{"paragraph":"ஆடு - பெயரடை"},{"paragraph":"pertaining to sheep"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English: </strong>From <a href=\"#/G4263 - πρόβατον - próbaton - prob'-at-on/4263\">G4263</a>; <i>relating to sheep</i>, that is, (a <i>gate</i>) through which they were led into Jerusalem: - sheep (market).</span>"},{"paragraph":""}]}